================================================================================
Third-party backend / weight license matrix
================================================================================

mlipgauge ships NO model weights. Real MLIP backends are optional extras,
installed on demand. Their model weights carry their own licenses, which the
user accepts when installing the corresponding extra. mlipgauge enforces an
allow-list at runtime (see src/mlipgauge/backends/base.py: BACKEND_LICENSES)
and refuses, fail-closed, to load a backend whose declared license is not on
the allow-list.

  Backend            Extra              Weight license     Commercial use
  -----------------  -----------------  -----------------  ---------------
  MACE-MP-0          pip install ...    MIT                yes
  CHGNet             [chgnet]           BSD-3-Clause       yes
  MatterSim          [mattersim]        MIT                yes
  mock (built-in)    (none)             Apache-2.0         yes  (deterministic, no weights)

DELIBERATELY EXCLUDED (not on the allow-list; loading is refused fail-closed):

  MACE-OMAT-0        --                 ASL (non-commercial)   NO

Rationale: the Academic Software License (ASL) used by some OMAT-trained
checkpoints forbids commercial use. To keep mlipgauge's default surface
unambiguously commercial-friendly (Apache-2.0), such checkpoints are excluded
from the built-in allow-list. A user may extend the allow-list explicitly and
thereby accept that license, but it is never enabled by default.

